Vectorize Data with Semantic Embeddings

In Data Cloud, you can create searchable semantic vector embeddings from your unstructured and structured data. Vector search helps your generative AI, automation, and analytics applications understand semantic similarities and context between embeddings.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: All Editions supported by Data Cloud. See Data Cloud edition availability.

A vector embedding is a numerical representation of a unit of text, often an article or a passage from a larger document, that is retrieved or used during a response generation. In Data Cloud, these units of text are referenced by chunk data model objects (CDMOs). Chunk DMOs are created from data model objects or unstructured data model objects. Emmbeddings are stored in index data model objects (IDMOs).

The embedding captures the semantic meaning of the content, so semantically similar items have similar embeddings. Embeddings are representations in a vector space that capture relationships between words or phrases. These representations enable machines to process and comprehend language effectively.

In Data Cloud, CDMOs and IDMOs are held in a data structure called a search index. After the vector embeddings are added to the search index, you can perform vector searches on that data from apps such as Prompt Builder, Einstein Copilot, or Tableau.
